data.title: What is the structure of benzole or benzol?
data.meta_description: Answer (1 of 2): Benzol and benzole are old terms for a coal-tar fraction that contained aromatic compounds, mostly benzene and toluene, which could be used to power internal combustion engines, at first on its own and later as an anti-knock ingredient.
